stor III|John J. Astor, Jr.]]<ref>The custom of the time was to attach the suffix \"junior\" to the younger living family member of the same name, not keep it consistent.</ref>\n* Ltc Albert V. Colburn\n* Ltc Nelson B. Sweitzer\n* Ltc Edward McK. Hudson\n* Ltc Paul Von Radowitz\n* Maj Herbert Von Hammerstein\n* Maj William W. Russell (USMC)\n* Maj [[:fr:Ferdinand Lecomte|Ferdinand Lecompte]] (Swiss Army Engineer)\n* Cpt [[George A. Custer]]\n* Cpt [[Joseph Kirkland]] \n* Cpt Arthur McClellan\n* Cpt [[Prince Philippe, Count of Paris|Louis Philippe d'Orleans]]\n* Cpt [[Prince Robert, Duke of Chartres|Robert d'Orleans]]\n* Cpt [[Martin T. McMahon]]\n* Cpt William P. Mason, Jr.\n* Cpt William F. Biddle\n* Cpt Edward A. Raymond\n|-\n|}\n\n===[[II Corps (ACW)|II Corps]]===\nBG [[Edwin Sumner]], Commanding\n<br>&nbsp;Ltc Joseph H. Taylor, Adjutant\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=25% | Division\n! width=25% | Brigade\n! Regiments and others\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |\nFirst Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Israel B. Richardson]]\n| First Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Oliver O. Howard]]\n|\n* [[5th New Hampshire Volunteer Infantry|5th New Hampshire]]: Col [[Edward E. Cross]]\n* [[81st Pennsylvania Infantry|81st Pennsylvania]]: Col James Miller\n* [[61st New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|61st New York]]: Col [[Francis C. Barlow]]\n* [[64th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|64th New York]]: Col Thomas J. Parker\n|-\n| [[Irish Brigade (U.S.)|Second Brigade]]\n&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Thomas Francis Meagher]]\n|\n* [[69th Infantry Regiment (New York)|69th New York]]: Col [[Robert Nugent (officer)|Robert Nugent]]\n* [[63rd New York Infantry|63rd New York]]: Ltc [[John Burke (colonel)|John Burke]]\n* [[88th New York Infantry|88th New York]]: Col Henry M. Baker\n|-\n| Third Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[William H. French]]\n|\n* [[52nd New York Volunteer Infantry|52nd New York]]: Col Paul Frank\n* [[57th New York Volunteer Infantry|57th New York]]: Col [[Samuel K. Zook