vania Infantry|88th Pennsylvania]]: ? || Fort Good Hope\n|-\n| [[99th Pennsylvania Infantry|99th Pennsylvania]]: Col Peter Fritz || Fort Mahon\n|-\n| 2nd New York Light Artillery: ? \n| \n* [[Fort Ward (Virginia)|Fort Ward]] (present-day Alexandria)\n* [[Fort Worth, Virginia|Fort Worth]] (present-day Alexandria)\n* [[Fort Reynolds (Virginia)|Fort Blenker]] (present-day [[Fairlington, Arlington, Virginia|Fairlington]])\n|-\n| \n* 107th Pennsylvania: Col Thomas A. Zeigel\n* [[54th Pennsylvania Infantry|54th Pennsylvania]]: Col [[Jacob M. Campbell]] \n| Kendall Green (present-day [[Gallaudet University]])\n|-\n| \n* Dickenson's Light Artillery (16th Independent New York Battery)\n* [[86th New York Volunteer Infantry|86th New York]]: Col Benajah P. Baily\n* Detachment of [[88th Pennsylvania Infantry|88th Pennsylvania]]: Col George P. McLean \n| East of the Capitol\n|-\n| \n* [[1st Regiment Massachusetts Heavy Artillery|1st Massachusetts Heavy Artillery]]: Col Thomas R. Tannatt\n* 56th Pennsylvania: Col Sullivan A. Meredith\n| \n* [[Fort Albany (Arlington, Virginia)|Fort Albany]]\n* Fort Tillinghast\n* [[Fort Richardson (Arlington, Virginia)|Fort Richardson]]\n* [[Fort Runyon]]\n* [[Fort Jackson (Virginia)|Fort Jackson]]\n* Fort Barnard\n* [[Fort Craig (Virginia)|Fort Craig]]\n* [[Fort Scott (Arlington, Virginia)|Fort Scott]] (all in present-day Arlington)\n|-\n| \n* Detachment of [[4th U.S. Artillery]]: ?\n* [[37th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|37th New York]]: Col [[John McCunn|John H. McCunn]]\n| [[Fort Washington Park|Fort Washington]] (present-day [[Fort Washington, Maryland]])\n|- \n|\n* [[97th New York Volunteer Infantry|97th New York]]: Col Charles W. Wheelock\n* 101st New York: Col Enrico Fardella\n* <s>[[91st New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|91st New York]]: Col Jacob Van Sandt</s><ref>Listed by McClellan as present at the time of the Peninsula campaign, [http://dmna.state.ny.us/historic/reghist/civil/infantry/91stInf/91stInfMain.htm though it had already departed for Florida]</ref>\n* [[12th West Virginia Volunteer Infantry Regiment|12th Virginia]]: Col John B. Klunk \n| [[Fort Corcoran]] (present-day [[Rosslyn, Virginia|Rosslyn]])\n|-\n|}\n<br>''Railroad Guards''\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Col [[Dixon S. Miles]]\n* 6th New York Cavalry (Cos. A, B, C, E, G, I, K, & M dismounted): Col [[Thomas Devin]]\n* <s>10th New York Cavalry (dismounted): Col John Lemmon</s><ref>Listed by McClellan as present at the time of the Peninsula campaign, [http://dmna.state.ny.us/historic/reghist/civil/cavalry/10thCav/10thCavMain.htm though it was actually in Gettysburg at the time and would not join the Department of the Potomac until August.]</ref>\n* 11th New York Cavalry (dismounted): Col James B. Swain\n* [[2nd Pennsylvania Cavalry]] (dismounted): Col Richard Butler Price\n\n===Troops Around Baltimore===\n<small>On March 22, the Middle Department was created with authority over Pennsylvania, New Jersey, Delaware, and the Eastern Shore of Maryland and Virginia, as well as the Maryland counties of Cecil, Hartford, Baltimore, and Anne Arundel. Dix remained in command.</small>\n\nMG [[John Adams Dix|John A. Dix]], Commanding\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Maj [[Daniel Tompkins Van Buren]], Chief of Staff and Acting Assistant Adjutant General\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Type of Units !! Regiments and others\n|-\n| \nCavalry \n| \n* [[1st Maryland Cavalry, U.S.A.|1st Maryland Cavalry]]: Cpt Henry A. Cole?\n* Purnell (Maryland) Legion Cavalry: Cpt Robert E. Duvall\n|-\n| \nArtillery \n| \n* Battery I, [[2nd U.S. Artillery]]: ?\n* [[Battery A, Maryland Light Artillery]]: Cpt John W. Wolcott\n* Battery L, 1st New York Artillery: Cpt John A. Reynolds\n* Independent Battery ?, Pennsylvania Artillery: ?\n* Independent Battery ?, Pennsylvania Artillery: ?\n|-\n| \nInfantry \n| \n* [[3rd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|3rd New York]]: Col Samuel M. Alford\n* [[4th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|4th New York]]: Col Alfred W. Taylor\n* [[11th Pennsylvania Infantry|11th Pennsylvania]]: Col [[Richard Coulter (general)|Richard Coulter]]\n* [[87th Pennsylvania Infantry|87th Pennsylvania]]: Col George Hay\n* 111th Pennsylvania: Col Matthew Schlaudecker\n* Detachment, [[21st Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|21st Massachusetts]]: ?\n* [[2nd Delaware Volunteer Infantry|2nd Delaware]]: Col W. Henry Wharton\n* [[2nd Maryland Infantry|2nd Maryland]]: Col John Sommer\n* 1st Eastern Shore Home Guard (Maryland): Col James Wallace\n* 2nd Eastern Shore Home Guard (Maryland): Col Robert S. Rogers\n* Purnell (Maryland) Legion Infantry: Col Samuel L. Graham\n|}\n\n==Department of Virginia==\n<small>The Department of Virginia constituted an area 60 miles from Fort Monroe. McClellan had received permission to absorb it into his army as a division of the First Corps, but it was rescinded shortly after he arrived on the Peninsula.</small>\n\nMG [[John E. Wool]], Commanding\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=25% | Location\n! Regiments and others\n|-\n| [[Fort Monroe]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMaj Joseph Roberts\n|\n* [[10th New York Infantry|10th New York]]: Col [[John E. Bendix]]\n* [[99th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|99th New York]] (2 cos.): Maj Richard Nixon\n* 7th Independent Battery, Massachusetts Artillery: Cpt Phineas Alonzo Davis\n* Detachment, 4th U.S. Artillery: ?\n* [[2nd Independent Battery Wisconsin Light Artillery|2nd Independent Battery, Wisconsin Artillery]]: Cpt Ernst F. Herzberg\n* [[4th Independent Battery Wisconsin Light Artillery|4th Independent Battery, Wisconsin Artillery]]: Cpt John F. Vallee\n|-\n| Camp Hamilton\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Max Weber (general)|Max Weber]]\n|\n* [[1st Regiment Delaware Volunteer Infantry|1st Delaware]]: Col John W. Andrews\n* [[16th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|16th Massachusetts]]: Col Powell T. Wyman\n* [[1st Michigan Volunteer Infantry Regiment (3 Years)|1st Michigan]]: Col [[John C. Robinson]]\n* [[20th New York Volunteer 