ork)|69th New York]]: Col [[Robert Nugent (officer)|Robert Nugent]]\n* [[63rd New York Infantry|63rd New York]]: Ltc [[John Burke (colonel)|John Burke]]\n* [[88th New York Infantry|88th New York]]: Col Henry M. Baker\n|-\n| Third Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[William H. French]]\n|\n* [[52nd New York Volunteer Infantry|52nd New York]]: Col Paul Frank\n* [[57th New York Volunteer Infantry|57th New York]]: Col [[Samuel K. Zook]]\n* [[66th New York Volunteer Infantry|66th New York]]: Col Joseph C. Pinckney\n* [[53rd Pennsylvania Infantry|53rd Pennsylvania]]: Col [[John R. Brooke]]\n|-\n| Artillery\n|\n* Batteries A & C, [[4th U.S. Artillery]]: Cpt Francis N. Clarke\n** Six Napoleons\n* [[Battery G, 1st New York Light Artillery|Battery G, 1st New York Artillery]]: Cpt John D. Frank\n** Six 10-lb Parrotts\n* Battery B, 1st New York Artillery: Cpt Rufus D. Pettit\n** Six 10-lb Parrotts\n* Battery A, 2nd New York Artillery:<ref>Later renamed 14th Independent Battery New York Artillery</ref> Cpt William H. Hogan\n** Six 10-lb Parrotts\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |\nSecond Division\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[John Sedgwick]]\n| First Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Willis A. Gorman]]\n|\n* 2nd New York State Militia:<ref>In May the 90-day regiment would be mustered out and then mustered in as the [[82nd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|82nd New York]], a three-year regiment</ref> Col George W.B. Tompkins\n* [[15th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|15th Massachusetts]]: Col [[Charles Devens]]\n* [[1st Minnesota Volunteer Infantry|1st Minnesota]]: Col [[Alfred Sully]] \n|-\n| [[Philadelphia Brigade|Second Brigade]]\n&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[William Wallace Burns]]\n|\n* [[69th Pennsylvania Infantry|69th Pennsylvania]]: Col [[Joshua T. Owen]]\n* [[71st Pennsylvania Infantry|71st Pennsylvania]]: Col [[Isaac J. Wistar]]\n* [[72nd Pennsylvania Infantry|72nd Pennsylvania]]: Col [[DeWitt Clinton Baxter]]\n* [[106th Pennsylvania Infantry|106th Pennsylvania]]: Col [[Turner G. Mor