ixth Corps (Provisional)]] on May 18, 1862.</small>\n\n===[[XII Corps (Union Army)|Fifth Corps]]===\n<small>On April 4, the Fifth Corps was renamed the Department of Shenandoah with authority over Maryland between the Blue Ridge and Flintstone Creek, Virginia between the Blue Ridge and the modern-day border with West Virginia.</small>\n\nMG [[Nathaniel P. Banks]], Commanding\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Cpt Louis H. Pelouze, Acting Assistant Adjutant General\n\n''Unattached Infantry''\n* 28th Pennsylvania: Col [[John W. Geary]]\n* 4th Regiment Potomac Home Brigade (Maryland): ?\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! width=25% | Division\n! width=25% | Brigade\n! Regiments and others\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |\nFirst Division\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Alpheus S. Williams]]\n| First Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Dudley Donnelly\n|\n* [[28th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|28th New York]]: Ltc Edwin F. Brown\n* [[5th Connecticut Infantry Regiment|5th Connecticut]]: Col George D. Chapman\n* [[46th Pennsylvania Infantry|46th Pennsylvania]]: Col [[Joseph F. Knipe]]\n* [[12th Regiment Indiana Infantry (1 year)|12th Indiana]]: ?\n* [[13th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|13th Massachusetts]]: Col Samuel H. Leonard\n|-\n| Second Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[John Joseph Abercrombie]]\n|\n* [[12th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|12th Massachusetts]]: Col [[Fletcher Webster]]\n* [[2nd Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|2nd Massachusetts]]: Col [[George H. Gordon]]\n* [[16th Indiana Infantry Regiment|16th Indiana]]: ?\n* [[1st Maryland Infantry, Potomac Home Brigade|1st Potomac Home Brigade (Maryland)]]: Col William P. Maulsby\n* [[114th Pennsylvania Infantry|Zouaves d'Afrique]] (one company): Cpt [[Charles H. T. Collis]]\n|-\n| Third Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[George Henry Gordon]]\n|\n* [[83rd New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|83rd New York]]: Col John W. Stiles\n* 29th Pennsylvania: Col John K. Murphy\n* [[27th Regiment Indiana Infantry|27th Indiana]]: