ia Cavalry]]: Col Henry Anisansel\n|-\n|}\n<small>Shields' Division was transferred to the Department of the Rappahannock on May 10, 1862</small>\n\n===District of Washington===\nBG [[James S. Wadsworth]], Commanding\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Regiments and others !! Camp Location\n|-\n| [[1st New Jersey Volunteer Cavalry|1st New Jersey Cavalry]]: Col [[William Halstead]] || Alexandria City\n|-\n| [[4th Pennsylvania Cavalry]]: Col James H. Childs || East of the Capitol\n|-\n| [[10th New Jersey Volunteer Infantry|10th New Jersey]]: Col William Bryan || Bladensburg Road\n|-\n| [[104th New York Volunteer Infantry|104th New York]]: Col John Rohrbach || [[Kalorama Heights]]\n|-\n| [[1st Wisconsin Heavy Artillery Regiment|1st Wisconsin Heavy Artillery]]: ? || Fort Cass ([[Arlington County, Virginia|Alexandria Co.]])\n|-\n| New York Artillery (three batteries): ?\n| \n* [[Fort Ethan Allen (Arlington, Virginia)|Fort Ethan Allen]] (Alexandria Co.) \n* [[Fort Marcy Park|Fort Marcy]] ([[Fairfax County, Virginia|Fairfax Co.]])\n|-\n| Depot of New York Light Artillery: ? || Camp Barry\n|-\n| 2nd District of Columbia: Col Charles M. Alexander || Washington City\n|-\n| 26th Pennsylvania: Col William F. Small || G Street Wharf\n|-\n| [[26th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|26th New York]]: Col William H. Christian || [[Fort Lyon (Virginia)|Fort Lyon]] (present-day [[Huntington, Virginia|Huntington]])\n|-\n| 95th New York: Col George H. Biddle || Camp Thomas \n|-\n| \n* 94th New York: Col Henry K. Viele\n* Detachment of [[88th Pennsylvania Infantry|88th Pennsylvania]]: Maj George W. Gile\n| Alexandria City\n|-\n| [[91st Pennsylvania Volunteer Infantry|91st Pennsylvania]]: Col Edgar I. Gregory || Franklin Square Barracks ([[Franklin Square (Washington, D.C.)|Franklin Square]])\n|- \n| [[4th New York Heavy Artillery Regiment|4th New York Heavy Artillery]]: Col [[Thomas D. Doubleday|T.D. Doubleday]]\n| \n* Fort Carroll (present-day [[Joint Base Anacostia-Bolling]]) \n* [[Fort Greble]] (also present-day JBAB)\n|-\n| 112th Pennsylvania: Col Charles Angeroth || Fort Saratoga\n|- \n| [[76th New York Volunteer Infantry|76th New York]]: Ltc John D. Shaul || [[Fort Stevens (Washington, D.C.)|Fort Massachusetts]] (Washington Co.)\n|- \n| [[59th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|59th New York]]: Col William L. Tidball || [[Fort Reno Park|Fort Pennsylvania]] ([[Tenleytown]])\n|-\n| Detachment of [[88th Pennsylvania Infantry|88th Pennsylvania]]: ? || Fort Good Hope\n|-\n| [[99th Pennsylvania Infantry|99th Pennsylvania]]: Col Peter Fritz || Fort Mahon\n|-\n| 2nd New York Light Artillery: ? \n| \n* [[Fort Ward (Virginia)|Fort Ward]] (present-day Alexandria)\n* [[Fort Worth, Virginia|Fort Worth]] (present-day Alexandria)\n* [[Fort Reynolds (Virginia)|Fort Blenker]] (present-day [[Fairlington, Arlington, Virginia|Fairlington]])\n|-\n| \n* 107th Pennsylvania: Col Thomas A. Zeigel\n* [[54th Pennsylvania Infantry|54th Pennsylvania]]: Col [[Jacob M. Campbell]] \n| Kendall Green (present-day [[Gallaudet University]])\n|-\n| \n* Dickenson's Light Artillery (16th Independent New York Battery)\n* [[86th New York Volunteer Infantry|86th New York]]: Col Benajah P. Baily\n* Detachment of [[88th Pennsylvania Infantry|88th Pennsylvania]]: Col George P. McLean \n| East of the Capitol\n|-\n| \n* [[1st Regiment Massachusetts Heavy Artillery|1st Massachusetts Heavy Artillery]]: Col Thomas R. Tannatt\n* 56th Pennsylvania: Col Sullivan A. Meredith\n| \n* [[Fort Albany (Arlington, Virginia)|Fort Albany]]\n* Fort Tillinghast\n* [[Fort Richardson (Arlington, Virginia)|Fort Richardson]]\n* [[Fort Runyon]]\n* [[Fort Jackson (Virginia)|Fort Jackson]]\n* Fort Barnard\n* [[Fort Craig (Virginia)|Fort Craig]]\n* [[Fort Scott (Arlington, Virginia)|Fort Scott]] (all in present-day Arlington)\n|-\n| \n* Detachment of [[4th U.S. Artillery]]: ?\n* [[37th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|37th New York]]: Col [[John McCunn|John H. McCunn]]\n| [[Fort Washington Park|Fort Washington]